<p>
  If a property does cater to a specific population segment, it will say so on their website.  Sometimes, a property only allows that segment (a common example is seniors-only housing).  Select only that population segment in the data entry form.  Other times, a property sets aside some number of units for a certain segment while leaving the other units available to all (a common example is reserving some units for developmentally disabled tenants).  In this case, select both general population <i>and</i> developmentally disabled.
</p>
